<title>BRAZIL: Brazil to let CVRD workers buy shares at auction.</title>
<headline>Brazil to let CVRD workers buy shares at auction.</headline>
<dateline>SAO PAULO 1997-01-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Brazilian government will allow the employees of state mining giant Companhia Vale do Rio Doce to participate in the auction of a 45 percent voting stake in the company, Gazeta Mercantil newspaper said.</p>
<p>Gazeta said the new rule would be included in the bid specifications for Vale's selloff to be approved in the next meeting of the National Privatization Council (CND).</p>
<p>According to the original selloff plan, CVRD workers would be allowed to acquire up to 5.11 percent of Vale's total capital, representing 10 percent of the government's stake in the company, at an offer which would follow the block sale of a 45 percent voting stake, the newspaper said.</p>
<p>Vale's privatization, previously due to begin in the first quarter, is now expected to start in April.</p>
<p>--Fatima Cristina, Sao Paulo Newsroom 5511 2485412</p>
